article.description: Vernon Taylor scored 22 points and Will Weathers had 19 as Troy knocked off North Texas 89-81 Saturday.
article.headline: Tristan Thompson's 25 not enough as North Texas falls
article.linkText: Thompson's 25 not enough as North Texas falls
article.story: TROY, Ala. -- Vernon Taylor scored 22 points and Will Weathers had 19 as Troy knocked off North Texas 89-81 Saturday night to win two games in a row for the first time this season. There were 10 ties and 13 lead changes in a rematch of the 2010 Sun Belt Conference Tournament title game that the Mean Green won 66-63. Tied at 52, the Trojans (4-13, 2/3 Sun Belt Conference) went on a 13-0 run to take control, shooting 68.4 percent from the field in the second half (13 of 19). North Texas (14-4, 3-2), which led 44-38 late in the first half, got within six on three occasions, the last at 84-78. Troy then hit 5 of 6 free throws. Travis Lee added 13 points on 5-of-5 shooting for the Trojans, who beat Western Kentucky 82-68 Thursday. Tristan Thompson's 25 points off the bench led the Mean Green and George Odufuwa had his 25th career double-double with 11 points and 12 rebounds.
